For what it's worth, the very beginning about the skull bone articulations, rib articulations, and pubic bone articulations are incorrect. Sutures in the skull and costochondral joints are both Synarthroses- meaning they do not move. The pubic symphysis is an amphiarthroses which means it is slightly mobile, not immobile.
